00:22:46.616 --> 00:22:50.216
I have a couple questions. I don't know if there's any studies, but do you think

385
00:22:50.236 --> 00:22:54.076
having mastitis or any infection during breastfeeding could even

386
00:22:54.136 --> 00:22:57.236
increase these T cells or have any effect?

387
00:22:59.476 --> 00:23:03.216
It's highly plausible that this all contributes to the

388
00:23:03.576 --> 00:23:06.636
localized T cell recruitment and infiltration, yes.

389
00:23:07.056 --> 00:23:11.016
So you think, for example, in mice that are pathogen-free, we wouldn't see that big

390
00:23:11.076 --> 00:23:14.556
increase of T cells or it's just the

391
00:23:15.236 --> 00:23:17.416
remodeling of the epithelial in the mammary gland?

392
00:23:18.416 --> 00:23:19.416
They're all excellent questions.

393
00:23:19.476 --> 00:23:22.796
We probably think it's a combination, but we do believe the remodeling of the

394
00:23:22.856 --> 00:23:26.536
mammary gland post lactation and pregnancy lactation

395
00:23:26.576 --> 00:23:30.516
involution does contribute to the recruitment of T cells,

396
00:23:30.576 --> 00:23:30.796
yes.

397
00:23:30.936 --> 00:23:34.636
Okay. And last question. More pregnancies makes you

