00:44:43.258 --> 00:44:46.438
here, is thinking about what this might mean in the setting of

767
00:44:46.478 --> 00:44:49.858
endocrine-resistant disease, for example, tumors with ESR1 mutations.

768
00:44:50.798 --> 00:44:53.548
Because at a high level, what we've seen here is that

769
00:44:54.378 --> 00:44:58.278
CDK4/6 inhibitors can also activate this estrogen receptor response

770
00:44:58.338 --> 00:45:02.038
in ESR1 mutant tumors. But now, if you're treating the tumor with

771
00:45:02.118 --> 00:45:05.718
ineffective endocrine therapy, like an aromatase inhibitor, for

772
00:45:05.778 --> 00:45:08.258
example, you're not able to neutralize that response.

773
00:45:08.738 --> 00:45:12.178
Cyclin D1 levels remain elevated, and it can promote

774
00:45:12.738 --> 00:45:16.038
earlier outgrowth of cells in the face of treatment.

775
00:45:17.538 --> 00:45:21.418
If you were to switch over to a drug that can effectively degrade the mutant

776
00:45:21.518 --> 00:45:22.598
ER, like a SERD,

777
00:45:23.398 --> 00:45:27.138
you can overcome this. Cyclin D1 levels go back down, and you get deeper cell

778
00:45:27.187 --> 00:45:31.178
cycle suppression. And again, in this context of ESR1 mutants, we

779
00:45:31.238 --> 00:45:34.698
also found that rather than switching the whole endocrine program, if you just

780
00:45:34.718 --> 00:45:38.658
knock down cyclin D1, you can also again deeply suppress the E2F target

781
00:45:38.698 --> 00:45:41.818
genes and restore tumor cell cycle control.

782
00:45:43.838 --> 00:45:46.518
And finally, I'm not going to talk about all this data, but I'll just mention

783
00:45:46.578 --> 00:45:49.298
briefly that we have also worked through the mechanism

784
00:45:50.298 --> 00:45:54.218
underlying this effect. So why would Rb going to these regions lead

785
00:45:54.278 --> 00:45:55.818
to the upregulation of genes?

786
00:45:56.978 --> 00:46:00.878
And we've done experiments such as IP-mass spec, looking for things that

787
00:46:00.898 --> 00:46:04.738
bind to Rb in the nucleus, and lots of chromatin profiling of

788
00:46:04.958 --> 00:46:07.988
a variety of different suspect factors that could be implicated.

789
00:46:08.638 --> 00:46:11.838
And the model that we've currently settled on can be summarized like this.

790
00:46:13.018 --> 00:46:16.978
Around these ER target genes, there are regions where the estrogen receptor is

791
00:46:17.038 --> 00:46:20.658
clearly bound, and in a complex with it is this histone demethylase

792
00:46:20.698 --> 00:46:24.138
KDM5A. I'm sure there are other factors as well.

793
00:46:24.178 --> 00:46:27.958
When we treat with a CDK4/6 inhibitor and Rb goes to the chromatin,

794
00:46:29.598 --> 00:46:33.198
it joins them, and we can see all three of these proteins interacting with each

795
00:46:33.278 --> 00:46:37.038
other. Now, this KDM5A is normally sitting at these

796
00:46:37.118 --> 00:46:39.758
genes and causing them to be partially repressed.

797
00:46:41.058 --> 00:46:44.877
When Rb comes and binds to KDM5A like this, it

798
00:46:44.958 --> 00:46:48.678
actually interferes with KDM5A's function, so you

799
00:46:48.718 --> 00:46:52.458
essentially relieve the repression of those ER target

800
00:46:52.478 --> 00:46:56.408
genes, and that is, we think, why these genes are getting upregulated with

801
00:46:56.438 --> 00:46:58.058
CDK4/6 inhibitor treatment.

802
00:47:00.078 --> 00:47:01.188
So to summarize then,

803
00:47:02.538 --> 00:47:06.218
as I've shown you, I think CDK4/6 inhibitors, we now see for the first time

804
00:47:06.278 --> 00:47:10.138
induce a very widespread redistribution of Rb

805
00:47:10.218 --> 00:47:13.938
along chromatin, not only to cell cycle gene promoters, but to

806
00:47:14.018 --> 00:47:15.728
other regions, most

807
00:47:16.718 --> 00:47:19.418
obviously around estrogen response target genes.

808
00:47:21.098 --> 00:47:25.038
And as I said, the most fascinating component of this to me is that

809
00:47:25.098 --> 00:47:28.718
we can see Rb very unexpectedly, not purely acting as a tumor

810
00:47:28.818 --> 00:47:32.158
